<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-03-20T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-03-20T12:00:00-05:00" n="273" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d273">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 839.51/1266.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Minister <persName type="to">Sullivan</persName>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-03-20T12:00:00-05:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">March 20, 1914, 12 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Cable immediately if there appears to be any apparent evidence on the
                            part of Congress to change its position as to authorization of loan or
                            if its position could be changed in reference to authorization of means
                            for the payment of back salaries only. The payment of back salaries
                            might be arrived at by a temporary advance of $500,000 <pb facs="0335" n="219" xml:id="pg_219"/> from public works funds on deposit in New
                            York if Congress would authorize the pledging of alcohol and stamp taxes
                            to repay this loan. If this is not possible request Minister of Finance
                            to prepare plan for efficacious repayment.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>